  [Text] The Environment Agency and the Japan Environment 
Association (director: Mutsumi Kato) will host "Symposium on 
Environmental Protection Vision" at the Tojo Kaikan on 30 
September. It is intended to promote the interests of people 
concerned with important issues involving environmental 
policies, focused this time on the "Use of and Problems With 
Economic Measures." University professors and local government 
administrators will discuss the carbon tax, the deposit charge 
system and paid garbage collection. Attendance is free of charge. 

